Join us at Digital First on 21 June

The event, hosted at Manchester Central, will connect public sector technology and procurement specialists with the best solution providers through plenary sessions, seminars and masterclasses. The event is for everyone who is involved in their organisation’s technology change or transformation, whether you’re the Head of ICT or a Financial Manager, there will be something for everyone.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
What to expect on the day

 

During the event, CCS will be hosting a variety of sessions to help add power to your technology procurement, including:

Plenary panel

  • Patrick Cahill, Deputy Director for Network Services at CCS will be discussing how we are helping to develop a digital future for the public sector. 

  • Phil Chatterton, Chief Enterprise Architect, Central Digital and Data Office will be discussing how Public Sector organisations can implement world-class self-service portals and IT workflows, overnight. 

  • Gill Stewart, Chief Digital Officer, Department for Levelling Up, Housing and Communities (DLUHC), will be speaking on ‘supporting modern resilient councils through digital transformation’.

Speaker sessions

  • ‘Customer focus, fix your service, help your users: A case study’ with Martin Sadler, Executive Director – IT & Digital, Sandwell and West Birmingham Hospitals NHS Trust

  • ‘Greater Manchester doing digital differently’ with Phil Swan, Director for Digital, Greater Manchester Combined Authority (GMCA)

  • ‘How Crown Commercial Service are helping to deliver a digital future’ with Patrick Cahill, Deputy Director of Network Services, CCS

  • ‘Driving Smarter Healthcare through Virtual Wards ‘ with Connie Hutchins, Senior Commercial Lead, CCS

Other speaker sessions include representatives from DLUHC, IT specialists from NHS Trusts, councillors from local governments and more. The day will also include breakout sessions from Socitm and Blackpool Council, LocalGov Drupal and more.

Meet the experts

These bitesize sessions will take place throughout the day, with a focus on specific products and services from our portfolio, including mobile voice and data services, vertical applications solutions, cyber and crown hosting virtual tours.

Interoperability panel

This session will introduce the work CCS is doing with the Government and Industry Interoperability Group (GIIG).

componentInstanceProperties.value:
Get involved


If you would like to come along, visit our website to book your complimentary space today. 
 

There’s also plenty more going on at the event. Take a look at the agenda to find out what’s on and when. You’ll also be able to access free tea, coffee and lunch on the day and there will be a networking drinks reception at the end of the day which you are welcome to join. 
 

If you would prefer to get in touch with our technology experts directly, simply fill out our form with your query.
 

We look forward to seeing you there.
